President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Nebraska and has ordered Federal assistance to supplement State and local recovery efforts. This declaration is in response to severe winter storms and straight-line winds that occurred from April 13 to April 18, 2018. Federal funding will be available to State and eligible local governments, as well as certain private nonprofit organizations, to help with emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. The counties affected by the severe weather include Antelope, Blaine, Boone, Boyd, Cheyenne, Clay, Custer, Deuel, Fillmore, Garfield, Gosper, Greeley, Hall, Hamilton, Holt, Howard, Keith, Knox, Logan, Loup, Madison, Merrick, Nance, Nuckolls, Pierce, Platte, Rock, Sherman, Valley, Webster, and Wheeler. Additionally, Federal funding will be available for statewide hazard mitigation measures. Constance C. Johnson-Cage has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas, and further designations may be made if requested by the State and warranted by damage assessments. For more information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.